commit.message: Use lamE instead of LamE to simplify and future-proof for GHC 9.10

Use TemplateHaskellQuotes instead of manually constructing Names

This will make the code far easier to maintain going forward. In addition, some
of the internal names that are referenced in
`Data.Functor.Invariant.TH.Internal` have changed in GHC 9.8, so using
`TemplateHaskellQuotes` makes the code robust against these changes.

Add Invariant(2) instances for more types from profunctors

`profunctors-5.6.1` adds `Functor` instances for various data types, so this
patch adds the corresponding `Invariant` instances. This also adds `Invariant2`
instances for `Copastro` and `Coyoneda`, which were previously omitted due to
an oversight.
Mention #24 in CHANGELOG, pre-emptive major version bump
Loosen constraint on instance Invariant2 Cokleisli
Loosen constraint on instance Invariant2 Kleisli
Mild code consolidation, mention #22 in CHANGELOG

commit.message:
Guard Option instance behind CPP

This is needed to make `invariant` build on GHC 9.2. See
https://gitlab.haskell.org/ghc/ghc/-/wikis/migration/9.2?version_id=318ba54dba47ed35d89648e027104cf766a63410#option-removed-from-datasemigroup.

Revert "Remove the Invariant Option instance"
